definition: A principle stating that if there are more objects than spaces, at least one space must contain more than one object.
A theorem stating that for any pair of people in a party, they are either friends, strangers, or enemies.
A function where each element of the domain is mapped to a unique element of the codomain.
A function where each element of the codomain is mapped to by at least one element of the domain.
A function that is both injective and surjective.
